- Sweet talker.

553
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:49,986
How many guys do you say this to?

554
00:40:50,360 --> 00:40:53,480
I can't keep giving
you a big tip, you know.

555
00:40:53,480 --> 00:40:54,808
Don't say that, or I'll get mad.

556
00:40:54,833 --> 00:40:56,265
Oh, why get mad?

557
00:40:58,280 --> 00:41:01,560
How many times have I told you?
I don't see you as a customer.

558
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:07,415
Okay, sorry! Like I said,
we're like brothers.

559
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:08,720
Why miss me so much?

560
00:41:10,480 --> 00:41:12,680
Gotta go now. I'm working.

561
00:41:15,439 --> 00:41:16,439
Ohn!

562
00:41:16,767 --> 00:41:17,767
Ohn!

563
00:41:24,564 --> 00:41:27,800
Not asleep yet?

564
00:41:28,680 --> 00:41:29,680
Not yet.

565
00:41:30,790 --> 00:41:33,046
I'm trying to draw some cartoons.

566
00:41:33,071 --> 00:41:35,923
Making those online stickers
like you suggested.

567
00:41:36,380 --> 00:41:37,406
Mmm-hmm.

568
00:41:38,317 --> 00:41:39,360
Oh...

569
00:41:40,852 --> 00:41:41,905
Agh...

570
00:41:44,893 --> 00:41:46,280
I went to see someone today.

571
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:53,560
And?

572
00:41:56,860 --> 00:41:59,280
Nah, not working out.

573
00:42:04,587 --> 00:42:05,864
I'm going to go shower.

574
00:42:05,889 --> 00:42:07,240
Oh wow.

575
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:28,400
Why can't I get in?

576
00:42:29,488 --> 00:42:30,880
Did he change the password?

577
00:42:47,122 --> 00:42:48,320
What is he doing?

578
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:51,040
Why doesn't he read my text?

579
00:42:56,362 --> 00:42:58,569
"Want to go to the massage parlor."

580
00:43:03,559 --> 00:43:04,800
Better not.

581
00:43:21,925 --> 00:43:22,925
Mmm.

582
00:43:23,902 --> 00:43:26,600
Hello. I'm Bomb.

583
00:43:29,080 --> 00:43:31,440
Jira. Nice to meet you.

584
00:43:33,280 --> 00:43:34,520
Shall we start?

585
00:43:49,826 --> 00:43:50,879
Mmm.

586
00:43:57,760 --> 00:44:00,080
Hey, my boyfriend's back!

587
00:44:00,104 --> 00:44:01,220
What?

588
00:44:01,245 --> 00:44:03,173
You said
you didn't have a boyfriend!

589
00:44:03,198 --> 00:44:05,330
If I told you, would you have come?

590
00:44:05,760 --> 00:44:08,476
I'm dead. He brought a gun too!

591
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:11,440
Stop!

592
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:14,240
I'm sorry. I really didn't know.

593
00:44:14,984 --> 00:44:16,760
I'm leaving right now.

594
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:17,960
Right now.

595
00:44:18,717 --> 00:44:19,880
You mess with my boyfriend?

596
00:44:20,698 --> 00:44:21,720
You die!

597
00:44:22,365 --> 00:44:23,920
Hey, wait. Don't!

598
00:44:23,945 --> 00:44:25,720
No. Don't!

599
00:44:25,720 --> 00:44:27,440
Don't...

600
00:44:33,360 --> 00:44:35,040
I'm kidding. It's okay.

601
00:44:37,655 --> 00:44:38,655
Gosh...

602
00:44:41,160 --> 00:44:43,600
It's already shriveled up as it is.

603
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:47,120
I'm joking. There's no gun.

604
00:44:48,440 --> 00:44:49,560
Maybe, something else.

605
00:44:50,680 --> 00:44:53,154
Come on, Golf. The three of us?

606
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:14,080
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

607
00:45:14,105 --> 00:45:16,320
♪ Can you feel... ♪

608
00:45:18,840 --> 00:45:23,940
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

609
00:45:23,965 --> 00:45:27,520
♪ Come rain or shine ♪

610
00:45:55,269 --> 00:45:57,986
I need a timeout.

611
00:45:58,011 --> 00:45:59,959
I... need to use bathroom.

612
00:45:59,984 --> 00:46:03,496
Sure. We'll add extra time for you.

613
00:46:03,520 --> 00:46:04,520
Okay.

614
00:46:34,517 --> 00:46:36,200
What the heck am I doing here?

615
00:47:44,805 --> 00:47:45,805
Who is it?

616
00:47:55,255 --> 00:47:56,403
Oh, JJ.

617
00:47:57,286 --> 00:47:58,442
How did you get here?

618
00:47:58,467 --> 00:48:01,647
You didn't read my text at all.
You can't just ghost me like this.

619
00:48:03,840 --> 00:48:06,280
Not too loud, JJ.
Come inside first.

620
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:13,960
Have a seat, and calm down.

621
00:48:17,059 --> 00:48:18,059
Ghosting what?

622
00:48:19,122 --> 00:48:20,360
I was just working.

623
00:48:27,053 --> 00:48:29,853
You underestimated me.
I really love you.

624
00:48:32,017 --> 00:48:33,396
You are my first love.

625
00:48:35,780 --> 00:48:36,780
What love?

626
00:48:38,240 --> 00:48:39,818
Don't be so dramatic.

627
00:48:39,842 --> 00:48:41,855
How old are you anyway?

628
00:48:41,880 --> 00:48:43,480
Twenty-two.

629
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:45,440
Twenty-five.

630
00:48:45,849 --> 00:48:47,165
Make up your mind.

631
00:48:47,189 --> 00:48:49,335
How old are you exactly?

632
00:48:49,360 --> 00:48:50,916
Let me see your ID card.

633
00:48:52,200 --> 00:48:53,200
Nope.

634
00:48:54,097 --> 00:48:57,575
JJ, if we're really going to date,

635
00:48:57,600 --> 00:48:59,520
we have to be
honest with each other.

636
00:49:01,360 --> 00:49:02,990
Show me your ID card.

637
00:49:13,797 --> 00:49:14,973
Hand it over.

638
00:49:25,486 --> 00:49:27,550
What? Only 19?

639
00:49:28,440 --> 00:49:29,816
You said 22.

640
00:49:30,406 --> 00:49:31,646
Yes, 19.

641
00:49:32,078 --> 00:49:34,443
Why did you have to lie?

642
00:49:41,319 --> 00:49:42,615
So do you live alone?

643
00:49:42,640 --> 00:49:43,640
No.

644
00:49:44,539 --> 00:49:45,699
I live with my boyfriend.

645
00:49:46,080 --> 00:49:47,080
What?

646
00:49:47,646 --> 00:49:49,916
What's the deal with you, Ohn?
You have a boyfriend?

647
00:49:51,717 --> 00:49:53,139
I asked you already.

648
00:49:54,863 --> 00:49:55,900
You didn't say anything.

649
00:49:56,770 --> 00:49:58,510
Why do I have to tell you?

650
00:50:02,574 --> 00:50:03,750
I'm back.

651
00:50:03,774 --> 00:50:06,719
Look, I bought so much
delicious unhealthy food,

652
00:50:06,744 --> 00:50:10,454
destroying our health.
All your favorites!

653
00:50:21,513 --> 00:50:22,730
Your nephew, Ohn?

654
00:50:25,208 --> 00:50:26,208
From which side?

655
00:50:30,560 --> 00:50:31,680
Not a nephew.

656
00:50:32,818 --> 00:50:34,561
This is JJ.

657
00:50:36,178 --> 00:50:39,000
And this is Jee, my boyfriend.

658
00:50:40,712 --> 00:50:42,480
Ohn, liar.

659
00:50:43,886 --> 00:50:45,424
I'm not okay with this.

660
00:50:45,449 --> 00:50:46,950
If you already have a boyfriend,

661
00:50:47,560 --> 00:50:48,600
then what am I?

662
00:50:50,240 --> 00:50:51,280
You choose now.

663
00:50:51,720 --> 00:50:52,720
Decide!

664
00:50:53,200 --> 00:50:54,200
Between me...

665
00:50:55,120 --> 00:50:56,120
and this old man.

666
00:50:58,956 --> 00:50:59,956
Make your choice!

667
00:51:02,394 --> 00:51:03,887
You can't trick me like this.

668
00:51:07,166 --> 00:51:09,960
What did you trick him about?

669
00:51:12,365 --> 00:51:13,411
Jeez...

670
00:51:15,487 --> 00:51:16,887
Because of my beauty, isn't it?

671
00:51:18,018 --> 00:51:20,400
Is this the time, Ohn?

672
00:51:23,200 --> 00:51:24,800
Ohn, I'm not laughing.

673
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:31,200
Take it easy, JJ.

674
00:51:32,640 --> 00:51:35,746
This old man thinks...
you should go home for now, JJ.

675
00:51:37,160 --> 00:51:38,906
Let's talk on Line later.

676
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:45,920
You'll message me, right?

677
00:51:47,130 --> 00:51:48,280
I will.

678
00:51:48,305 --> 00:51:49,600
- Promise?
- Mmm.

679
00:51:59,213 --> 00:52:00,800
Go on. I'll walk you out.

680
00:52:12,400 --> 00:52:13,400
Have some, Jee.

681
00:52:14,804 --> 00:52:15,901
Uh-uh.

682
00:52:15,926 --> 00:52:16,960
You didn't eat it often.

683
00:52:17,280 --> 00:52:18,280
Cheat day?

684
00:52:18,989 --> 00:52:19,989
Mmm.

685
00:52:22,914 --> 00:52:23,914
Hmm...

686
00:52:24,829 --> 00:52:27,032
- It's fresh.
- Mmm.

687
00:52:27,400 --> 00:52:29,200
Come on, you...

688
00:52:29,853 --> 00:52:31,937
Didn't you say you don't want it?

689
00:52:31,962 --> 00:52:33,935
But someone followed you
all the way to our room.

690
00:52:34,598 --> 00:52:35,627
Mmm...

691
00:52:35,652 --> 00:52:36,765
Well...

692
00:52:37,804 --> 00:52:40,669
I just tried looking like you said.

693
00:52:41,161 --> 00:52:43,581
But let's take a break for now.

694
00:52:43,605 --> 00:52:44,874
It's too messy.

695
00:52:45,640 --> 00:52:46,640
Mmm.

696
00:52:47,697 --> 00:52:49,760
Honestly, it's difficult, isn't it?

697
00:52:50,531 --> 00:52:51,436
Mmm.

698
00:52:51,461 --> 00:52:54,693
A, Job, and Pete are really lucky
they found each other.

699
00:52:54,718 --> 00:52:55,720
Mmm...

700
00:52:55,744 --> 00:52:56,822
Hey.

701
00:52:56,846 --> 00:52:58,750
Do you know I'd met someone?

702
00:52:59,310 --> 00:53:02,808
There were chains,
whips, and handcuffs

703
00:53:02,833 --> 00:53:04,788
and a blindfold too.

704
00:53:04,813 --> 00:53:05,864
Whoa.

705
00:53:07,345 --> 00:53:09,423
How was it? Did you like it?

706
00:53:11,503 --> 00:53:13,353
At first, it was exciting.

707
00:53:14,017 --> 00:53:17,334
But after a while,
I started to have second thoughts.

708
00:53:18,109 --> 00:53:20,073
And I felt like...

709
00:53:21,760 --> 00:53:23,680
I wasn't ready.
So I asked to leave.

710
00:53:24,180 --> 00:53:25,186
Oh.

711
00:53:25,536 --> 00:53:28,720
Wasn't he mad that you ran away?

712
00:53:30,040 --> 00:53:33,055
He didn't mind. He was sweet.

713
00:53:33,080 --> 00:53:34,629
He said I could go.

714
00:53:34,654 --> 00:53:36,561
And if I get the chance
or feel ready,

715
00:53:36,585 --> 00:53:37,986
I can come back to him.

716
00:53:38,011 --> 00:53:39,917
- Really?
- Mmm-hmm.

717
00:53:43,751 --> 00:53:46,079
I don't think
it's wrong or anything.

718
00:53:46,103 --> 00:53:47,431
But...

719
00:53:47,758 --> 00:53:49,413
I just felt weird.

720
00:53:49,858 --> 00:53:55,080
Maybe we grew up with the value
of having only one partner.

721
00:53:55,080 --> 00:53:57,723
Like Monogamy or something.

722
00:53:57,748 --> 00:54:01,156
Mmm. That might be it.

723
00:54:02,480 --> 00:54:06,615
But the funny thing is
people tend to think that

724
00:54:06,640 --> 00:54:09,975
gay people or people
with diverse gender identities

725
00:54:10,000 --> 00:54:11,560
like to switch partners

726
00:54:11,585 --> 00:54:15,225
or that Open Relationships
are normal for us.

727
00:54:15,250 --> 00:54:18,165
Even though, actually,
straight couples have...

728
00:54:18,190 --> 00:54:19,923
those kinds of relationships too.

729
00:54:19,948 --> 00:54:23,280
It's not like every couple like us

730
00:54:23,280 --> 00:54:25,455
is okay with this kind of thing.

731
00:54:25,480 --> 00:54:26,880
- True.
- Mmm.

732
00:54:27,170 --> 00:54:29,400
What now?

733
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:31,520
What do...

734
00:54:32,840 --> 00:54:33,886
we...

735
00:54:33,910 --> 00:54:35,473
do next?

736
00:54:39,064 --> 00:54:40,200
Mmm...

737
00:54:44,954 --> 00:54:47,400
No. Don't give up.

738
00:54:48,360 --> 00:54:52,467
One day, we'll meet
some good people.

739
00:54:54,425 --> 00:54:57,143
Then let's keep open to the idea.

740
00:54:58,320 --> 00:54:59,880
But don't rush it.

741
00:55:07,478 --> 00:55:08,520
Well...

742
00:55:09,563 --> 00:55:11,080
if we get physical with anyone...

743
00:55:12,107 --> 00:55:13,650
we have to tell each other first.

744
00:55:14,803 --> 00:55:18,647
And most importantly,
wear protection every time.

745
00:55:18,672 --> 00:55:20,428
- Okay?
- Same here.

746
00:55:21,279 --> 00:55:25,600
But I'm always waiting for you.

747
00:55:28,668 --> 00:55:29,792
Okay...

748
00:55:42,799 --> 00:55:43,799
Ew.

749
00:55:43,824 --> 00:55:45,600
- Salty?
- It's all mushy.

750
00:55:50,246 --> 00:55:52,815
"I never thought I'd have to
face something like this."

751
00:55:52,840 --> 00:55:55,520
"Is this the 7-Year Itch?"

752
00:55:56,026 --> 00:55:58,104
"But if it allows us
to keep loving each other"

753
00:55:58,129 --> 00:56:00,690
"and stay together,
then what does it matter?"

754
00:56:11,278 --> 00:56:15,615
Ooh! Kittima, the Sorceress
of the Enchanted City.

755
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:16,920
Ancient cartoon.

756
00:56:17,600 --> 00:56:22,055
I told you. We need to move
beyond Kittima already.

757
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:23,248
Why am I getting teased?

758
00:56:23,273 --> 00:56:28,920
- Ikkyu is a kathoey!
- Ikkyu is a kathoey!

759
00:56:28,920 --> 00:56:30,240
Don't say that.

760
00:56:30,880 --> 00:56:32,080
Why can't I say it?

761
00:56:32,880 --> 00:56:34,080
It's the truth.

762
00:56:34,440 --> 00:56:36,855
But you have to be strong.

763
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:38,080
You have to survive it.

764
00:56:38,105 --> 00:56:43,480
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

765
00:56:43,480 --> 00:56:46,540
♪ Calling out so we never part ♪

766
00:56:46,564 --> 00:56:49,440
Subtitle by Trirat Trakulphat
